@jfangm Small correction: Most of the old Halo-era Bungie devs who stayed at Microslop were some of the people who were "lower on the totem pole." The main guys who made Halo what it was like Jaime Griesemer, Jason Jones, Marty O' Donnell (and I argue Marty was one of the bigger ones if my theory that he did a lot more than just make the music is even somewhat true), Marcus Lehto, and a fair number of other people all left both Bungie and Microslop over the years.
Most of the guys from old Bungie who remained with Halo were people like Frank O' Connor, which I'll be nice in this and say even if they weren't idiots and everything, they let themselves get bossed around by people who got hired into 343i by Microslop who actively *hated* Halo conceptually (hence why I argue the Halo TV show was the embodiment of what 343i's people would've done if they owned Halo from the beginning). 
The ones who remained at 343i after Bungie ditched Halo were, for lack of better wording off the top of my head, "pushovers"/"yes men" at best and akin to my theory with why Game Freak fell off after Pokemon Gen 5 story writing wise at worst (the primary story guy, Junichi Masuda IIRC, was said to have ruled with an iron fist over the story writing and my theory is maybe he ruled with an iron fist over that stuff because everyone else at Game Freak was coming up with regarded ideas and Masuda was tired of it).
